;\\n\\n        if (defined != that.defined)\\n        {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        return value != null ? value.equals(that.value) : that.value == null;\\n    }\\n\\n    public int hashCode()\\n    {\\n        int result = super.hashCode();\\n        result = 31 * result + (defined ? 1 : 0);\\n        result = 31 * result + (value != null ? value.hashCode() : 0);\\n        return result;\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778103272225}]}\n../1502-ffc1a2ca/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk15on:1.70/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-06T21-35-41-286694Z.log:714:[thinking] I'm considering the active task only, and I'm wondering if the existing placeholder might be problematic. I’m thinking we could leave it for now? However, since all top-level classes should be public, it makes sense to address that. Yet, I want to avoid broad changes unless necessary.\n../1502-ffc1a2ca/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk15on:1.70/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-06T21-35-41-286694Z.log:716:[thinking] I’m realizing there may be a conflict with the placeholder not being a dynamic-access class. I should also ensure not to include a dollar sign in the file or class names. It'll be essential to inspect reports for any dynamic classes as well.\n../1502-ffc1a2ca/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk15on:1.70/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-06T21-35-41-286694Z.log:720:[tool-call] delta {\"path\":\"tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk15on/1.70/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\"limit\":200}\n../1502-ffc1a2ca/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk15on:1.70/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-06T21-35-41-286694Z.log:721:[tool-call] end id=call_nZIrOYVzoS01JLWNwLqmbffQ|fc_08698cc12b0e00360169fbb3f6146c8191a375cc7dc05c6925 name=read args={\"path\": \"tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk15on/1.70/build/reports/dynamic-