util-jdk15on/1.70/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access\\ntests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk15on/1.70/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/bcutil-jdk15on-1.70/reflection-calls.json\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778103559849}]}\n../1502-ffc1a2ca/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk15on:1.70/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-06T21-35-41-286694Z.log:2191:[thinking] **Exploring dynamic coverage issues**\n../1502-ffc1a2ca/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk15on:1.70/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-06T21-35-41-286694Z.log:2193:[thinking] I'm wondering why dynamic coverage isn't detecting executed APIs while Jacoco does. Maybe dynamic coverage only considers native runs, not JVM? It’s possible native executions weren't run after our recent changes. I should inspect the class report HTML to see if there's anything interesting.\n../1502-ffc1a2ca/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk15on:1.70/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-06T21-35-41-286694Z.log:2195:[thinking] If the dynamic coverage relies on metadata generated by the agent, it might not include certain executions. Perhaps the user-code filter is excluding some classes, which could complicate coverage matching. It really seems like reflection and class coordination could be contributing to these coverage issues.\n../1502-ffc1a2ca/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk15on:1.70/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-06T21-35-41-286694Z.log:2197:[thinking] **Analyzing coverage matching**\n../1502-ffc1a2ca/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk15on:1.70/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-06T21-35-41-286694Z.log:2199:[thinking] I think the coverage matching might link call sites to reflection target metadata organized by class. Since our target is bcprov and not bcutil, that could be why it's not counting for bcutil. I need to choose a target class within the bcutil artifact that has a public static method like getInstance(Object) but doesn't require ASN1Encodable as the type.\n../1502-ffc1a2ca/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk15on:1.70/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-06T21-35-41-286694Z.log:2207:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Exploring dynamic coverage issues**\\n\\nI'm wondering why dynamic coverage isn't detecting executed APIs while Jacoco does. Maybe dynamic coverage only considers native runs, not JVM? It’s possible native executions weren't run after our recent changes. I should inspect the class report HTML to see if there's anything interesting.\\n\\nIf the dynamic coverage relies on metadata generated by the agent, it might not include certain executions. Perhaps the user-code filter is excluding some classes, which could complicate coverage matching. It really seems like reflection and class coordination could be contributing to these coverage issues.\\n\\n**Analyzing coverage matching**\\n\\nI think the coverage matching might link call sites to reflection target metadata organized by class. Since our target is bcprov and not bcutil, that could be why it's not counting for bcutil. I need to choose a target class within the bcutil artifact that has a public static method like getInstance(Object) but doesn't require ASN1Encodable as the type.\\n\\nI should look for suitable classes in org.bouncycastle.oer that can work with ASN1Integer. Maybe `org.bouncycastle.oer.its.UINT8.getInstance(Object)` could be a good option? I’ll check those classes now!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_08698cc12b0e00360169fbb5095058819181bff3f099c0201d\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-7UQEqi5wcLFkUrY5OABZQ0htF6sZpafwMopo9-55RkhTHsiE_M6flEU0VJfFEk9OHjfiz1fifikEx5iiuNs5TKhQWAsQpascYBzGWDfGrpYPpPzw-pMfdaFl2QiZChI0KNM8oPsGpgsr1HrUL7QL9Pw8Twf-TrfIdsT2pVLDjeL9zz